Architecture plan for issues #119 and #120

Project shape:
- Next.js App Router frontend in src/app with server-rendered public pages and client-side admin components.
- Shared presentation helpers live in src/lib, including Markdown rendering in src/lib/markdown.ts and SEO helpers in src/lib/page-metadata.ts.
- Styling is Tailwind utility-based through className strings in page components and global styles in src/app/globals.css.

Issue #119: Display subspace/post route path labels in lowercase
- Scope is presentational only; no schema, API, or routing changes.
- Update the route/path label className strings in:
  - src/app/(public)/s/[slug]/[postId]/page.tsx
  - src/app/(public)/page.tsx
  - src/app/(public)/t/[slug]/page.tsx
- Remove only Tailwind uppercase utilities from slug/path labels so stored lowercase slugs render as-is.
- Preserve other typography/color/spacing classes and do not alter generated URLs.

Issue #120: Add heading typography to rendered markdown articles
- Scope is post detail rendering only.
- Update the Markdown article/prose container in src/app/(public)/s/[slug]/[postId]/page.tsx.
- Add nested Tailwind selectors for h1/h2/h3 sizing, font weight, and tight leading to override preflight resets while preserving existing margins and sanitized Markdown behavior.
- No dependency changes are expected because Markdown parsing/sanitization already exists.

Dependencies and sequencing:
- The issues are independent and both affect presentation.
- Issue #119 and #120 can be implemented in either order, but both touch post detail page className strings, so sequential edits should avoid overwriting adjacent class changes.
- Recommended verification for each issue: npm run lint, npm run typecheck, and targeted visual/manual inspection of the affected public routes when data is available.

Key design decisions:
- Keep changes localized to page component className strings.
- Avoid database/API/Rust changes.
- Do not introduce new components or shared abstractions for these small one-off styling fixes unless later issues expand the pattern.
